      },
      "privateNotes": "",
      "publicNotes": "<p><strong>Role:</strong> the innocent young painter Queen Ileosa frames for the king's murder — a recurring NPC, <strong>not</strong> an enemy. She avoids combat entirely, fleeing through the Shingles (Event 12). She is telling the truth: she did not kill the king.</p><p><strong>In the chase:</strong> she moves one obstacle at a time while she holds a lead, uses her wand on the closest PC, favors Acrobatics, and takes risks to gain ground when a PC closes. Cornered, she uses <em>Fit of Laughter</em> and weeps that she has been set up.</p>",
      "publication": {
        "title": "Pathfinder: Curse of the Crimson Throne (PF2e conversion, private)",
